properties.Elevation measurement method: Topographic map and digital elevation models
properties.Elevation comments: Samples were from river cut sections. Elevations were measured relative to the high water mark of the rivers. The elevation of the high water mark was referenced against topography maps with a contour interval of 10 m. The elevation contours on these maps are regarded as being very accurate, so measurements taken close to the contour lines were regarded as having an accuracy of close to 1 m, while between the contours it would be a maximum of 5 m. Per Möller says that in most cases, an uncertainty of +/-2 m is appropriate, which is what we are using.
properties.Comments\/details on MIS designation or: Although the age corresponds to MIS 5c, the authors regarded this as an underestimation and the deposit is MIS 5e in age.
properties.Acquisition parameters: direct measurements of the amount of radiation-induced paramagnetic centres from the shell and surrounding sediments
properties.Comments and notes: Species: Portlandia arctica. Sediments were marine facies.
